ont-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Low folate levels are typical of MTHFR mutations, and folate plays a crucial role alongside B12 in homocysteine metabolism. For those with a defective MTHFR enzyme, folic acid cannot be efficiently metabolized: </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK539712/" class="text-link" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">only 5-methyl-THF (methylfolate)</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> can participate in the conversion of homocysteine to methionine.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">For this reason, it is essential to avoid foods and supplements </span><a href="https://methyl-life.com/blogs/mthfr/methylfolate-vs-folic-acid" class="text-link"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">containing folic acid</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">. Folic acid is a synthetic form of the vitamin, which undergoes a multi-step conversion process in the body catalyzed by the MTHFR enzyme. </span><!--EndFragment--><br></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" id="r-1627477816446" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1627477816446" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" style="display: block; flex-wrap: unset; visibility: visible;" data-layout-lg="4+8" data-layout-md="4+8" data-layout-sm="12+12" data-layout-xs="12+12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-4 gf_col-md-4 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1625746964083" data-id="1625746964083" style="display: block; flex-direction: unset; justify-content: unset; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" id="e-1627477816382" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1627477816382" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/c3e45c59-7596-4b9e-bf1e-363867d86ed8/-/format/auto/-/preview/120x120/-/quality/lighter/Methyl-Life-Supplements.jpg" alt="Methyl Life Supplements" class="gf_image rte__no-indent gf_lazyload" data-gemlang="en" width="10" height="10" data-width="auto" data-height="auto" title="Methyl Life Supplements" natural-width="10" natural-height="10" data-lg-size="3000x3000"></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-8 gf_col-md-8 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1625828879986" data-id="1625828879986"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" id="r-1627477816365" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1627477816365" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1625828979467" data-id="1625828979467"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" id="e-1640681952673" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-head